The Assistant Manager for the Sustainable Singapore Gallery is multi-faceted role as it involves overseeing different aspects of the gallery, naming operations, programmes, events &amp; marketing. This is a supervisory position which requires the successful candidate to manage personnel at the gallery to ensure smooth operations, successful programme planning, effective events &amp; marketing.&nbsp;

Skills&nbsp;
The position requires you to be passionate about sustainability, familiar with various administrative practices and eager to participate in the design &amp; management of events, school programmes of the gallery. Candidates must also have management skills to oversee the gallery’s day-to-day running, dispatch tasks to the gallery’s staff, train interns and volunteer, plan schedules, set deadlines, etc. Interpersonal skills are also key for the position as one of the gallery manager’s role is to build working relationships with partners, statutory boards, schools, learners etc.

